{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5d343afd-3382-485a-84b3-a5f8c522cece","content":"Sheet‑Pan Lemon‑Herb Salmon with Chickpeas & Broccolini — quick, healthy, one‑pan (serves 3)\n\nTime: 25 min.\n\nIngredients: 3 salmon fillets, 1 can chickpeas (drained), 1 bunch broccolini (or broccoli florets), 1 lemon, 2 tbsp olive oil, 2 garlic cloves, 1 tsp dried oregano, salt, pepper, parsley.\n\nSteps: Preheat 425°F. Toss chickpeas + broccolini with oil, garlic, oregano, salt/pepper on sheet. Roast 12 min. Nest salmon on pan, drizzle lemon + oil, roast 8–10 min. Finish with parsley and extra lemon.\n\nWant a printable recipe or add ingredients to your grocery list?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"1a17012c-b763-4326-bbc1-c6cfc2a77e62","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"**Suggesting a dinner idea**\n\nThe user wants a quick, healthy dinner idea. Considering their household preferences, I’m thinking of a one-pan Mediterranean-style meal. I could suggest \"Sheet-pan lemon herb salmon with chickpeas and broccoli\" or \"Miso-glazed salmon with a quick cucumber salad.\" I'll include prep time, a brief reason why it's good, a short ingredient list, and quick steps. Plus, I can suggest optional substitutions and serving ideas. I can also offer to add this to their grocery list or meal plan!**Crafting a dinner suggestion**\n\nNo tools are needed right now, so I’ll make a concise dinner suggestion: \"Sheet-pan Lemon-Herb Salmon with Chickpeas & Broccolini.\" This dish takes about 20-25 minutes and is perfect for a pescatarian with Mediterranean flavors. The ingredients include salmon fillets, chickpeas, broccoli, lemon, olive oil, garlic, oregano, and salt/pepper. The steps are simple: preheat to 425°F, toss the vegetables and chickpeas, roast for 12 minutes, add the salmon, and roast until flaky. This serves about 3 and can be served over greens or quinoa!","encryptedContent":"","outputTokens":544},"id":"1a2bc5bf-092c-452d-885a-15edaece20ec","timestamp":"2026-03-12T